><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup.of\"><span class=\"name\">FreeAbelianGroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">of</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup\">FreeAbelianGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The canonical map from `α` to `FreeAbelianGroup α`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup.of","kind":"def","line":113,"name":"FreeAbelianGroup.of","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.lean#L113-L115"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#instUniqueFreeAbelianGroupOfIsEmpty\"><span class=\"name\">instUniqueFreeAbelianGroupOfIsEmpty</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/IsEmpty/Defs.html#IsEmpty\">IsEmpty</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Unique.html#Unique\">Unique</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup\">FreeAbelianGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#instUniqueFreeAbelianGroupOfIsEmpty","kind":"instance","line":107,"name":"instUniqueFreeAbelianGroupOfIsEmpty","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.lean#L107-L107"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#instInhabitedFreeAbelianGroup\"><span class=\"name\">instInhabitedFreeAbelianGroup</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup\">FreeAbelianGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#instInhabitedFreeAbelianGroup","kind":"instance","line":104,"name":"instInhabitedFreeAbelianGroup","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.lean#L104-L105"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup.addCommGroup\"><span class=\"name\">FreeAbelianGroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">addCommGroup</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup\">FreeAbelianGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup.addCommGroup","kind":"instance","line":101,"name":"FreeAbelianGroup.addCommGroup","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.lean#L101-L102"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup\"><span class=\"name\">FreeAbelianGroup</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `α` is a type, then `FreeAbelianGroup α` is the free abelian group generated by `α`.\nThis is an abelian group equipped with a function\n`FreeAbelianGroup.of : α → FreeAbelianGroup α` which has the following universal property:\nif `G` is any abelian group, and `f : α → G` is any function, then this function is\nthe composite of `FreeAbelianGroup.of` and a unique group homomorphism\n`FreeAbelianGroup.lift f : FreeAbelianGroup α →+ G`.\n\nA typical element of `FreeAbelianGroup α` is a formal sum of\nelements of `α` and their formal inverses.\nFor example if `x` and `y` are terms of type `α` then `x + x + x - y` is a\n\"typical\" element of `FreeAbelianGroup α`. In particular if `α` is empty\nthen `FreeAbelianGroup α` is isomorphic to the trivial group, and if `α` has one term\nthen `FreeAbelianGroup α` is isomorphic to `ℤ`.\nOne can think of `FreeAbelianGroup α` as the functions `α →₀ ℤ` with finite support,\nand addition given pointwise.\n\nTODO: rename to `FreeAddCommGroup` and introduce a multiplicative version\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.html#FreeAbelianGroup","kind":"def","line":77,"name":"FreeAbelianGroup","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/FreeAbelianGroup.lean#L77-L97"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Module.NatInt","Mathlib.GroupTheory.Abelianization.Defs","Mathlib.GroupTheory.FreeGroup.Basic","Mathlib.Control.Basic"],"instances":[{"className":"AddCommGroup","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.addCommGroup","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Inhabited","name":"instInhabitedFreeAbelianGroup","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Unique","name":"instUniqueFreeAbelianGroupOfIsEmpty","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Nontrivial","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.instNontrivialOfNonempty","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Monad","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.instMonad","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"LawfulMonad","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.instLawfulMonad","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"CommApplicative","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.instCommApplicative","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Mul","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.mul","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Distrib","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.distrib","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"NonUnitalNonAssocRing","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.nonUnitalNonAssocRing","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"One","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.one","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"NonUnitalRing","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.nonUnitalRing","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Ring","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.ring","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"CommRing","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.instCommRingOfCommMonoid","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]},{"className":"Unique","name":"FreeAbelianGroup.pemptyUnique","typeNames":["FreeAbelianGroup"]}],"name":"Mathlib.GroupTheory.FreeAbelianGroup"}